24/02/2005
STRASBOURG, France -- Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe (PACE) President Rene Van der Linden on Wednesday (23 February) praised the results of weekend parliamentary elections in the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus (TRNC), saying the outcome demonstrated Turkish Cypriots' "European orientation" and their "wish to end the division of the island". 
Also on Wednesday, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan reiterated that Ankara would consider formal recognition of Cyprus only after a final settlement is reached under UN auspices. 
(CoE Web site, NTV, TurkishPress.com- 23/02/05)
